Case Study: WannaCry Ransomware Attack
Introduction

WannaCry was a ransomware attack that spread worldwide in May 2017. It encrypted files on infected computers and demanded payment in Bitcoin to restore access.

What Happened?

The malware exploited a vulnerability in Microsoft Windows systems. It rapidly spread across networks, infecting over 200,000 computers in more than 150 countries.

Which CIA Principle Was Affected?
Confidentiality

Sensitive information became inaccessible.

Integrity

Files were encrypted, altering their original state.

Availability

Users could not access their systems or files.

Impact
Hospitals canceled surgeries.
Businesses experienced downtime.
Financial losses reached billions of dollars.
Critical services were disrupted.
Prevention
Install security updates.
Regularly back up important data.
Use antivirus software.
Avoid suspicious email attachments.
Enable firewalls.
Conclusion

The WannaCry attack highlighted the importance of regular software updates, backups, and strong cybersecurity practices.